# employee-factory Google OAuth scope bundles (full-set responses)

## Trigger

Apply when Grant asks for:

- Google OAuth scopes
- Google Auth Playground URLs
- refresh-token scope setup
- "what scopes do we need" for an employee-factory agent (Joanne, etc.)

## Required response behavior

- Always provide the **full current scope bundle** for the requested agent's supported Google vertical tools.
- Do **not** provide only newly added scopes.
- If a scope set changes, explicitly provide the refreshed full set.
- Include scopes as copy-paste-ready URL lines for Google Auth Playground.

## Joanne scope bundle (current canonical set)

Joanne supports two Google verticals in employee-factory:

- Gmail send-email tooling
- Google Docs create-doc tooling (with Drive permissions grant)

Always provide all three scopes together:

- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.send`
- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/documents`
- `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.file`

## Output format contract (when asked)

When returning scopes for Joanne, include:

1. A short "full Joanne bundle" heading.
2. One code block with the three scope URLs (one per line) for direct paste into Auth Playground.
3. A one-line reminder that the refresh token must be re-issued with the full set when scopes change.
